\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the mandatory System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) and secure software engineering requirements for Elko County.
 This policy ensures that information security and privacy controls are systematically integrated into the acquisition,
 development,
 implementation,
 and maintenance of all county information systems,
 thereby protecting Elko County data and Criminal Justice Information (CJI) from unauthorized access,
 modification,
 or destruction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County employees,
 contractors,
 external service providers,
 and vendors involved in the specification,
 design,
 development,
 acquisition,
 testing,
 implementation,
 and modification of information systems,
 software,
 and system components that process,
 store,
 or transmit Elko County data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the executive approval authority for major system acquisitions,
 development tasks requiring official county clearance,
 and formal risk acceptance of policy exceptions including intellectual property deviations and unsupported component exceptions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall manage day-to-day SDLC compliance tasks.
 This includes defining security and privacy roles within SDLC phases,
 integrating risk management into daily operational activities,
 reviewing developer processes and tools,
 and validating that system developers execute secure development processes prior to deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Department Personnel / System Developers
\series default
:
 Shall execute software development and system integration tasks utilizing agency-documented security and privacy engineering principles in strict alignment with this policy.
 External Service Providers shall perform required testing,
 remediate identified flaws within the timeframes defined in Section 6.4,
 and provide all documentation defined in Section 6.2 prior to system acceptance.
\end_layout

