\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) Baseline
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County shall manage information systems using a formally defined System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) that incorporates information security and privacy considerations at every phase,
 from initiation through disposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that security and privacy roles and responsibilities are explicitly defined and assigned prior to the initiation of any SDLC project.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall integrate the organizational information security and privacy risk management process into all SDLC activities prior to system authorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Individuals executing SDLC tasks must possess the necessary skills and technical competencies corresponding to their assigned roles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All system preproduction environments,
 including development,
 test,
 and integration environments,
 shall be protected commensurate with risk throughout the system development life cycle,
 consistent with NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 SA-3(1).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Acquisition Process and Contracting (Hard Gate)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Prior to executing contracts or initiating development involving third-party systems or external service providers,
 the procurement workflow must successfully pass the Supply Chain Risk Management and IT Financial Management stage gates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All SDLC acquisitions shall satisfy the vendor risk assessments and technical approvals mandated by ECIO 
\series bold
Policy 
