\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Critical severity
\series default
 (CVSS score 9.0–10.0):
 remediated within 15 days;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
High severity
\series default
 (CVSS score 7.0–8.9):
 remediated within 30 days;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Medium severity
\series default
 (CVSS score 4.0–6.9):
 remediated within 60 days;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Low severity
\series default
 (CVSS score 0.1–3.9):
 remediated within 90 days.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 End of Life and Unsupported System Components
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County information systems and system components shall be proactively replaced or upgraded when the developer,
 vendor,
 or manufacturer ceases to provide analytical support,
 software updates,
 or security patches.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
IT Department personnel shall replace system components when support is no longer available,
 or shall establish in-house support or obtain contractual vendor support as an alternative.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Retained unsupported components must be fully isolated from public and uncontrolled networks by placement in segmented,
 access-controlled network zones with documented compensating controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Retained unsupported components must operate under a documented Risk Acceptance Memo satisfying all criteria defined in Section 6.8.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Intellectual Property and Source Code Ownership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To ensure the continuous security,
 maintainability,
 and auditability of Elko County systems:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All software,
 source code,
 scripts,
 configurations,
 and related intellectual property engineered or developed by Elko County employees shall remain the exclusive and sole property of Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All software and related intellectual property developed by External Service Providers,
 contractors,
 or vendors utilizing Elko County systems,
 funding,
 or data shall become the exclusive property of Elko County upon creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Pre-Commencement Exception Gate
\series default
:
 Any deviation from this ownership model —
 including commercial-off-the-shelf software licensing,
 shared-rights agreements,
 or vendor retention of underlying IP —
 must be explicitly documented in a legally binding contract and authorized via a Risk Acceptance Memo signed by the IT Director prior to the initiation of the project or procurement.
 Development or deployment shall not commence without this formalized clearance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Unsupported Component Exception Criteria
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To obtain a Risk Acceptance Memo for an unsupported system component,
 the Assistant IT Director must verify and document that all of the following conditions are satisfied:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Business Criticality
\series default
:
 The component supports a mission or business function for which no operationally equivalent replacement exists,
 as documented in a written business impact analysis approved by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Market Survey
\series default
:
 IT Department personnel must conduct and document a formal market survey within the preceding 90 calendar days confirming that no vendor-supported replacement product is commercially available that meets the functional requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Network Isolation
\series default
:
 The component must be logically and physically isolated from all public and uncontrolled networks,
 residing in a dedicated,
 access-controlled network segment with no direct inbound or outbound internet connectivity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compensating Controls
\series default
:
 IT personnel must document and implement compensating controls —
 including at minimum application whitelisting,
 enhanced monitoring,
 and restricted physical and logical access —
 sufficient to reduce residual risk to a level accepted by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Review Frequency
\series default
:
 The IT Director must review and reauthorize the exception no less than every 365 calendar days.
 Exceptions failing to satisfy all criteria shall be immediately revoked,
 requiring component decommissioning within 90 calendar days.
\end_layout

